 from simon giaeb cc monash edu au simon shields subject sspx schism organization monash university melb australia lines seven eight hi all hope you all had a blessed easter i have a document which i believe refutes the notion that the sspx society of saint pius x is in schism or that there has been any legitimate excommunication if anyone is interested in reading the truth about this matter please email me and i ll send them the document via email its two six pages long so i wont be posting it on the news group its titled neither schismatic nor excommunicated this article was originally an english translation by the society of saint pius x in ireland from the french journal courrier de rome the french article in its turn was a translation from the italian of the roman newsletter si si no no this booklet contains the transcription with some minor editing of the irish article and was transcribed and produced by john clay townsville queensland australia there is no copyright attached simon shields contents neither schismatic nor excommunicated one catholics on the rack one the choice of the sensus fidei three ambiguity four the church is not bicephalous two headed six the person and the function of the pope six unity of faith and unity of communion eight the criteria of choice one zero ecumenism an attack on the unity of the church one zero the extraordinary situation within the church one one extraordinary duties of lay people one two duties and powers of bishops one four from the fact of their greater duties one four from the fact of their greater power one four the power and the duty of the papacy one five the election of bishops one five state and right of necessity one six one there is in the church a real state of necessity one seven for souls one eight for seminarians one eight two all the ordinary means have been exhausted one nine three the act itself is not intrinsically evil and there resul two one four in the limits of effective requirements two two five the authority of the pope is not put into question two three the excommunication two four conclusion two five bibliography two six three one god bless ye all an irish fairwell may the road rise to meet you may the wind be always at your back may the sun shine warm upon your face the rains fall soft upon your fields and until we meet again may god hold you in the palm of his hand simon p shields programmer viva cristo rey monash university college gippsland ph six one five one two two six three five seven jhs switchback rd churchill fax six one five one two two six three zero zero australia three eight four two internet simon giaec cc monash edu au m j